******
[3]
Date: Mon 5 Jul 2010
Source: Kyodo News [edited]
<http://home.kyodo.co.jp/modules/fstStory/index.php?storyid=510391>


A cow in the city of Miyazaki has tested positive for FMD in gene
tests after showing symptoms of the livestock disease, including
excessive salivation, the farm ministry said Monday [5 Jul 2010].

The Miyazaki prefectural government had slaughtered and buried all 16
cows bred at the same farm by Monday morning [5 Jul 2010] before the
results of the gene tests were known, local government officials said.

With the new case, the prefectural government will have to postpone
its plan to declare an end to the outbreak in the southwestern
Japanese prefecture from 16 Jul 2010 to 27 Jul 2010, at the earliest.
[The full story requires subscription].

